## Enumeration

### nmap — Full Port Scan

A default nmap scan only covers the top 1000 ports. On OSCP machines and CTFs alike, services are frequently placed on non-standard ports to catch lazy scanners. Always run a full port scan.

```bash
nmap -sV -sC -p- --min-rate 5000 <target-ip>
```

```
PORT      STATE SERVICE VERSION
80/tcp    open  http    nginx 1.16.1
6498/tcp  open  ssh     OpenSSH 7.6p1
65524/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.43
```

Three services. Two web servers on non-standard ports. Both need to be enumerated independently.

