## Steganography

The web content includes a reference to an image file. Downloaded images should always be checked for hidden data when other avenues are exhausted.

```bash
# Download the image
wget http://<target-ip>:65524/<image-path>/binarycodepixabay.jpg

# Attempt steghide extraction (no passphrase or use cracked password)
steghide extract -sf binarycodepixabay.jpg -p "mypasswordforthatjob"

# Extracted file contains SSH credentials
cat secrettext.txt
# username: boring
# password: <binary encoded string>
```

```bash
# Decode binary to ASCII
echo "01101001 01100011 ..." | python3 -c "
import sys
binary = sys.stdin.read().strip().split()
print(''.join([chr(int(b, 2)) for b in binary]))
"
# Result: SSH password
```

